    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing eq_drb_to_setup function in F1AP library\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP library was missing the `eq_drb_to_setup` function which is needed for comparing DRB setup configurations. This caused issues when trying to validate DRB setup parameters during UE context management procedures.\n\nThe function was expected to exist based on the existing naming conventions and usage patterns in the codebase but was never implemented. This led to compilation errors and runtime issues when modules tried to use this function.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_common.h`: Added function declarations for all new equality functions including `eq_drb_to_setup` and `eq_f1ap_drb_to_be_setup`\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_common.c`: Implemented all required equality functions with proper NULL pointer handling and complete structure comparison\n\nThe implementation follows the existing patterns in the F1AP library and provides both the properly named function and the exact name mentioned in various parts of the codebase.\n"
}